The paper discusses a methodology for determining the difficulty level of factual questions generated from ontologies, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of Item Response Theory (IRT) in the methodology suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions educational and professional applications, indicating a potential connection to computer science education (cs.EDU).
